        <h2>Handling Common Download Hurdles</h2>
        <p>During the peak season—usually 10 to 14 days before examinations commence—the Univindia portal experiences massive traffic surges. If you find the site unresponsive or encounter a "Record Not Found" error, try these troubleshooting tips. First, ensure you have entered your details exactly as they were in your application form. Second, clear your web browser's cache or try using a different browser (like Google Chrome in 'Incognito' mode). Third, if the server is timing out, try accessing the portal during "quiet hours," such as between midnight and 6 AM. Many students also find that searching by 'Form Number' is more reliable than searching by name during high-traffic periods.</p>

